# Converting ECharts Examples

When adding a chart from https://echarts.apache.org/examples/en/:

## Copy

- The `option = { ... }` object (series, xAxis, yAxis, tooltip, legend, grid)
- Data arrays and formatting config

## Skip — these are handled by BaseChart

- `document.getElementById(...)` → BaseChart uses `useRef`
- `echarts.init(...)` → BaseChart handles this
- `chart.setOption(...)` → BaseChart handles this
- `chart.dispose()` → BaseChart handles cleanup
- `$.get(...)`, `fetch(...)`, jQuery → handle data loading outside the component

## Translate to props

Turn hardcoded values into readable props:

```tsx
// ECharts example has:
//   smooth: true, lineStyle: { width: 3 }, areaStyle: { opacity: 0.4 }

// Expose as:
export type LineSeriesConfig = {
  smooth?: boolean;    // instead of raw ECharts smooth
  lineWidth?: number;  // instead of lineStyle.width
  showArea?: boolean;  // instead of checking areaStyle existence
  areaOpacity?: number; // instead of areaStyle.opacity
};
```
